content: A walk to the Seine and back from another day. Part 5 of 6. River itself, vegetation around, and a wooden towpath alongside it.

photos.alt: A photo of the river, close up onto some vegetation growing from it, with some smaller shrubs, grass, small trees. Some reddish branches, some bigger submerged logs. There is a slight wind that makes stripes over the water, with the grass and shrubs reflecting in it. It is possible to see a bit of a reflection of the trees from the other side in the water as well.

A photo of a riverside with a wooden towpath going over the green grass. There are many green trees with occasional yellow leaves, and a bit of the river can be seen on the left. Further, the towpath splits and a metal fence starts to protect the waterside. The wooden planks of the towpath are slightly shiny from the small past rain, and there are some yellow leaves lying around on it.

A photo of a dense vegetation on the other side of the river — or, actually, on an island. Large trees with occasional thin dead branches stand on top of the water, with some of their branches submerged. On the right of the photo it can be slightly seen how the river goes around that green island.

A photo of a riverbank, with a glimpse of a bridge behind the trees. In the middle of the frame a few trees are surrounded by the water, there is some grass and various flowers on top of the water as well: yellow and light purple. There are slight waves from the wind, and a blurry out of focus tree hugging the frame from the left side.
